Introduction to Functions / Methods

    A method = block of reusable code.

    Helps in avoiding repetition, improves readability and maintainability.

    Example: Instead of writing a+b everywhere, make a sum() method.

Syntax & Declaration

General structure of a method:
        returnType methodName(parameters) {
            // method body
            return value;  // if returnType is not void
        }
Example:
        int sum(int a, int b) {
            return a + b;
        }

Purpose & Usage

        Reduces code duplication

        Improves modularity → divide program into smaller parts

        Makes debugging easier

Method Components

        Return Type → void, int, boolean, String, etc.

        Parameters → values passed into the method (Java is pass-by-value).

        Calling a Method → inside main(), like:
            int result = sum(10, 20);
            System.out.println(result);

Practice Examples

        TypeFunction method (print "Hello Sidd!")

        Sum of numbers

        Swap function (using temp or without temp)

        Prime number check

        Armstrong number check

